lost in it's sonorous repetition. Consciousness returned to her slowly, as if she had lain long asleep, and <br>
cognition slower still. Fragments of thought flowed through her mind like the ripples through the <br>
subterranean pools, only to fade away into the darkness. Flashes of memory illuminated her thought like the <br>
glimmering of reflected moonlight, only to dim away as the gloom returned.  Imperceptably at first, then faster <br>
the shadows lifted, and light returned.<br>
<br>
Focus rushed outwards from her nose as her vision rapidly cleared, taking in all as it did so. <br>
<br>
A notched blade. A partially dismantled corpse. A congealing pool of blood. A golden boot.<br>
<br>
Feeling returned in a rush along with recognition, and a single sob wracked her frame.  With a croak from damaged <br>
vocal cords she mouthed a soft plea.<br>
<br>
'Elixar, help me'.<br>
<br>
